title: Liverpool forced to make humiliating Twitter change after Man Utd win EFL Cup
text:
Liverpool forced to make humiliating Twitter change after Man Utd win EFL Cup LIVERPOOL have been forced to change their Twitter bio after Manchester United won the EFL Cup. PUBLISHED: 18:48, Sun, Feb 26, 2017 | UPDATED: 19:43, Sun, Feb 26, 2017 
United began the game with 43 major honours in their illustrious history. 
And had the chance to go level with Liverpool on 44. Reuters Manchester United's Paul Pogba celebrates with the trophy TWITTER Liverpool's Twitter bio before Manchester United won at Wembley Man United player ratings against Southampton in the EFL Cup final Sun, February 26, 2017 Click through the gallery for the Man United player ratings against Southampton TWITTER Liverpool's Twitter bio after Manchester United won at Wembley 
Before the match, Liverpool's Twitter bio described the club as 'England's most successful club with 41 major honours'. 
But after Zlatan Ibrahimovic 's late winner the bio no longer mentions the amount of trophies they have won. GETTY Zlatan Ibrahimovic scored a late winner for Manchester United 
Liverpool are unlikely to add to their total this season as they are 14 points behind Chelsea in the Premier League and out of every other competition. 
But United are still in the Europa League and FA Cup. Related articles
